dct_description_sm: Plates from the publisher's An illustrated historical atlas of the state of Minnesota.; Region shown extends from Lake of the Woods in the north to Mille Lacs lake in the south.; Shows county boundaries, sections, owners of large parcels, Indian reservations, railroad lines.; "182" and "183" at the upper margins of the sheet.; Includes two inset maps: Lake of the Woods continuation -- Lake County continuation.; Ancillary maps on verso:  Map of Douglas and Pope Counties -- Counties of Clay, Wilkin, Becker, Otter Tail, and part of Wadena. "184" and "181" at upper margins.
43 x 69 Centimeters on sheet 45 x 71 Centimeters
